課程大綱Course syllabus




　　　　　　　　
This course is designed to introduce various English technical writing formats and requirements to computer science and engineering students. It provides some basic training to improve students English writing and organization skills. Lectures and workshops are conducted in English. There are in-class exercises, quizzes, and homework written assignments. Students are expected to participate actively in lectures, workshops, group discussions, and presentation sessions.




課程目標 Objectives




　　　　　　　　
1)	Introduce various technical writing formats and requirements2)	Provide general guidelines for technical writing3)	Improve students general English writing and organization skills4)	Strengthen students communication and presentation skills5)	Enhance students’ proof-reading ability by reviewing common mistakes in technical writing6)	Prepare students to write their journal papers, theses, or dissertation in English




授課方式 Teaching methods




　　　　　　　　
•	Lectures •	Workshops •	Group Discussions(Lectures and Workshops are all in English.)




評分方式﹝評分標準及比例﹞Evaluation (Criteria and ratio)等第制單科成績對照表 letter grading reference





　　　　　　　　
1.Oral Presentation：10%2.Workshops：10%3.Writing Assignments：20%4.Mid-term：20%5.Final exam：30%6.Quizzes：10%




參考書/教科書/閱讀文獻 Reference book/ textbook/ documents
〔請遵守智慧財產權觀念，不可非法影印。教師所提供之教材供學生本人自修學習使用,不得散播及做為商業用途〕
